The paper deals with welfare maximization in two-sided markets using mechanisms, which is a topic in game theory (cs.GT) and microeconomic theory (cs.EC). The paper also discusses the complexity of the optimal feasible mechanism, which is related to computational complexity (cs.DS) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The paper presents results on the expected welfare of the Buyer Trade Reduction (BTR) mechanism, which is a machine learning algorithm (cs.LG) used in the context of two-sided markets.
